projectScope.summary:
The Project is the proposed fuel abatement clearing and release of an 11-ha land parcel within the 311 ha McGowan lands Agricultural Reserve 2004-0433. The land will be released for the purpose of non-soil based arable agriculture. Three 2 ha areas and one 3.2 ha area will be leased to successful applicants.
This Project is located at km 151 of the South Klondike Highway, approximately 28 km South of Whitehorse, and will be accessed by Mosquito Road. The Project is within the Kwanlin Dün First Nation Territory.
Development of the parcels will be completed by the successful applicants and may occur between April 15 and November 30. The project is assessed based on a 30-year lease length maximum as per the Lands Act; activity duration is dependent on sublease duration.&nbsp;

