The Project is the construction and operation of a septic field to treat and dispose of domestic wastewater generated from an existing maintenance camp. The Project is located at the Mayo Generating Station, approximately 5 km north of the Village of Mayo within the Territory of the Na-Cho Nyak Dun.
The proposed septic field will replace the existing wastewater holding tank system currently used to manage domestic wastewater generated from the existing maintenance camp accommodations at the Mayo Generating Station. As the site is an existing camp with access, lot preparation has already been completed (i.e. access roads, clearing) and will not be required.
Access to the Project will occur via the Siver Trail Highway, Wareham Dam Road and the Silver Springs Road. Construction of the septic field is anticipated to begin in 2026 once ground conditions are suitable (approximately from June 1 to Sept 1) and is expected to take approximately one week to complete. The septic field will remain in place for up to 50 years. Camp occupancy and associated activities up to 120 people have been previously assessed under YESAA (2009-0040). The proposed septic field is designed to accommodate wastewater from occupancies of up to 220 people to meet current and potential future needs; occupancy in excess of 120 people has not been previously assessed and would be subject to applicable assessment and permitting requirements at that time. Increases to camp occupancy is not proposed as part of this project.&nbsp;

