projectScope.summary:
The Project, Mitchell Road Industrial Area Master Plan, is the development of an industrial subdivision to provide development opportunities within the Town of Faro. The proposed development will include the construction of two new roads, the installation of power and telecommunications along the road right-ofway, ditched drainage along the road right-of-way, and the legal subdivision and survey of lots. The project also includes a geotechnical borehole program to establish the sub-base construction for the proposed roads.&nbsp;
The project location is accessed via Mitchell Road. The total development area encompasses 9.57 ha. Within that area, there will be nine small lots (0.25-0.5 ha), six medium lots (0.5-0.75 ha) and two large lots (0.75-1.0 ha). The Project is located within the Town of Faro and is within the Territories of both the Ross River Dena Council and Liard First Nation.&nbsp;
Project activities are anticipated to occur over two phases. Phase 1 includes construction of a straight road for the development of eight industrial lots; a cul-de-sac at the end of the straight road; and an outfall ditch at the northwest corner of the subdivision. Phase 2 includes the construction of a curved road, requiring the cul-de-sac from Phase 1 to be converted to an intersection. Phase 2 will only occur once there is sufficient demand for the lots. Each phase is anticipated to take up to 2 construction seasons. Except for clearing, construction activities will occur between May and October. Clearing of vegetation will occur outside of the bird nesting season (May 1-August 31). Note: clearing, grading, and development of lots will not occur as part of this project; this will be the responsibility of lot purchasers.&nbsp;

